King salmon.joke: I caught a king salmon! Checkmate!

Gar.joke: Yar! It's a gar! Har har!

Sea bass.joke: No, wait- it's at least a C+!

Sea cucumber.joke: I got a sea cucumber! It's a bit cumbersome...
Sea cucumber.fact: They are marine animals with a leathery skin and an elongated body containing a single, branched gonad. Sea cucumbers are found on the sea floor worldwide.

Gigas giant clam.joke: I got a gigas giant clam! Its kind of a big deal.
Gigas giant clam.fact: The giant clams are the members of the clam genus Tridacna that are the largest living bivalve mollusks. There are actually several species of giant clams in the genus Tridacna.

Spider crab.joke: I got a spider crab! Water bugs can rest easy.
Spider crab.fact: The Japanese spider crab (Macrocheira kaempferi) is a species of marine crab that lives in the waters around Japan. It has the largest known leg-span of any arthropod.

Flarefin koi.fact: Flarefin Koi are only caught in lava, the Lavaproof Fishing Hook, Hotline Fishing Hook, or any pole using Underworld Critters as bait must be used to catch them.

Blobfish.joke: This odd creature floats above the ocean floor, consuming any edible material in its path.
Blobfish.fact: The Blobfish is a fish that can be caught in the submarine ride at the Night Market.

Crimsonfish.joke: Lives deep in the ocean but likes to lay its eggs in the warm summer water.
Crimsonfish.fact: The Crimsonfish is a fish that can be caught in the ocean at The Beach during Summer. It is one of the five Legendary Fish.

Anglerfish.fact: They are bony fish named for their characteristic mode of predation, in which a modified luminescent fin ray (the esca or illicium) acts as a lure for other fish.

Ms angler.fact: Ms. Angler can be found in the river in Pelican Town north of JojaMart.
